4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would exempt Crime Stoppers of Metro
6 Alabama, Incorporated, from payment of state sales and
7 use taxes and would provide an option for
8 municipalities and counties to provide an exemption
9 from local sales and use taxes.
10
11
12 A BILL
13 TO BE ENTITLED
14 AN ACT
15
16 Relating to sales and use taxation; to exempt Crime
17 Stoppers of Metro Alabama, Incorporated, from paying state
18 sales and use taxes; and to provide the option for counties
19 and municipalities to exempt this entity from local sales and
20 use taxes.
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
22 Section 1. (a) Crime Stoppers of Metro Alabama,
23 Incorporated, is exempted from paying state and local sales
24 and use tax.
25 (b) The exemption provided in this section may apply to
26 county or municipal sales and use taxes upon approval of a
27 resolution or ordinance adopted by the local governing body
28 pursuant to Section 40-23-4.01, Code of Alabama 1975.
